{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775853665192,"sessionID":"ses_286dfbbecffeOwTX0YtXPNLrkv","part":{"id":"prt_d79207234001RqFR6BiWeNBO9Q","messageID":"msg_d79205c5d001jIsCynWlTG0ZT3","sessionID":"ses_286dfbbecffeOwTX0YtXPNLrkv","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_393baf3cf2164e2cb51d4cb6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification — AR-012: Session Store Interface\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **Module:** `pkg/store`  \n6: **Language:** Go  \n7: **Size:** S  \n8: **Type:** New feature — Session persistence layer for sandbox orchestration\n9: \n10: ---\n11: \n12: ## Requirements & Scenarios\n13: \n14: ### REQ-001: Store Interface Contract\n15: \n16: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a `Store` interface implemented by Redis and Valkey providers with methods: `Ping`, `GetSandboxBySessionID`, `StoreSandbox`, `UpdateSandbox`, `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`, `ListExpiredSandboxes`, `ListInactiveSandboxes`, `UpdateSessionLastActivity`, and `Close`.\n17: \n18: #### Scenario: Ping verifies connectivity\n19: - **GIVEN** a healthy Redis/Valkey server\n20: - **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n21: - **THEN** the implementation issues PING and requires string response `PONG`\n22: \n23: #### Scenario: Store interface implemented by Redis\n24: - **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE=redis`\n25: - **WHEN** `Storage()` is called\n26: - **THEN** the returned `Store` is `*redisStore` implementing all 9 methods\n27: \n28: #### Scenario: Store interface implemented by Valkey\n29: - **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE=valkey`\n30: - **WHEN** `Storage()` is called\n31: - **THEN** the returned `Store` is `*valkeyStore` implementing all 9 methods\n32: \n33: ---\n34: \n35: ### REQ-002: Not Found Semantics\n36: \n37: **Requirement:** The system SHALL return package error `ErrNotFound` (message `store: not found`) when a session key is absent on read or when last-activity update targets a missing session.\n38: \n39: #### Scenario: Get missing session returns ErrNotFound\n40: - **GIVEN** no key `session:{id}` in backend\n41: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, id)` runs\n42: - **THEN** error is `ErrNotFound` (Redis: `redis.Nil`; Valkey: `IsValkeyNil`)\n43: \n44: #### Scenario: Update last-activity on missing session\n45: - **GIVEN** no key `session:{id}` in backend\n46: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, id, time.Now())` is called\n47: - **THEN** error is `ErrNotFound`\n48: \n49: ---\n50: \n51: ### REQ-003: Session Key Naming\n52: \n53: **Requirement:** The system SHALL use string prefix `session:` concatenated with the session id as the primary key for JSON document storage.\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: Key construction\n56: - **GIVEN** session id `abc-123`\n57: - **WHEN** the store writes sandbox data\n58: - **THEN** the string key is `session:abc-123`\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: ### REQ-004: Expiry Index (Sorted Set)\n63: \n64: **Requirement:** The system SHALL maintain sorted set key `session:expiry` with member = session id and score = `ExpiresAt` Unix seconds. `StoreSandbox` SHALL add the member with the sandbox expiry score. `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` SHALL remove the member.\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: StoreSandbox adds to expiry index\n67: - **GIVEN** a new sandbox with `ExpiresAt = time.Unix(1000, 0)`\n68: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` succeeds\n69: - **THEN** `session:expiry` contains member `sandbox.SessionID` with score `1000`\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: List expired uses ZRANGEBYSCORE\n72: - **GIVEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` with limit > 0\n73: - **WHEN** the implementation queries the index\n74: - **THEN** it selects members with scores from `-inf` through `before.Unix()`, limited to `limit` entries\n75: \n76: #### Scenario: DeleteSandboxBySessionID removes from expiry index\n77: - **GIVEN** session `abc` exists in `session:expiry` ZSET\n78: - **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc\")` succeeds\n79: - **THEN** `session:expiry` no longer contains member `abc`\n80: \n81: ---\n82: \n83: ### REQ-005: Last-Activity Index (Sorted Set)\n84: \n85: **Requirement:** The system SHALL maintain sorted set key `session:last_activity` with member = session id and score = last activity Unix seconds. `StoreSandbox` SHALL ZADD with score `time.Now().Unix()` on initial store. `UpdateSessionLastActivity` SHALL ZADD with the provided timestamp. `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` SHALL ZREM the member.\n86: \n87: #### Scenario: StoreSandbox initializes last-activity\n88: - **GIVEN** a new sandbox being stored at time `T`\n89: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` succeeds\n90: - **THEN** `session:last_activity` contains member `sandbox.SessionID` with score `T.Unix()`\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: List inactive uses activity index\n93: - **GIVEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)`\n94: - **WHEN** executed\n95: - **THEN** members with last-activity score ≤ `before.Unix()` are returned up to `limit`\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: UpdateSessionLastActivity bumps timestamp\n98: - **GIVEN** session `abc` with last-activity score `1000`\n99: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"abc\", time.Unix(2000, 0))` succeeds\n100: - **THEN** `session:last_activity` member `abc` has score `2000`\n101: \n102: #### Scenario: DeleteSandboxBySessionID removes from activity index\n103: - **GIVEN** session `abc` exists in `session:last_activity` ZSET\n104: - **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc\")` succeeds\n105: - **THEN** `session:last_activity` no longer contains member `abc`\n106: \n107: ---\n108: \n109: ### REQ-006: StoreSandbox Atomicity and Validation\n110: \n111: **Requirement:** The system SHALL reject nil sandbox or zero `ExpiresAt`. The system SHALL execute SETNX on session key, ZADD expiry, and ZADD last_activity in one pipeline/multi block. The system SHALL fail if any command in the batch errors.\n112: \n113: #### Scenario: Nil sandbox rejected\n114: - **GIVEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)`\n115: - **WHEN** called\n116: - **THEN** error indicates sandbox is nil (no backend operation)\n117: \n118: #### Scenario: Zero ExpiresAt rejected\n119: - **GIVEN** sandbox with `ExpiresAt = time.Time{}` (zero value)\n120: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n121: - **THEN** error indicates ExpiresAt is invalid (no backend operation)\n122: \n123: #### Scenario: Duplicate store fails (SETNX)\n124: - **GIVEN** session `abc` already exists in backend\n125: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` with same `SessionID` is called\n126: - **THEN** operation fails (SETNX returns 0)\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: Pipeline atomicity\n129: - **GIVEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` with valid data\n130: - **WHEN** pipeline executes SETNX, ZADD expiry, ZADD last_activity\n131: - **THEN** all three succeed or all fail; no partial writes\n132: \n133: ---\n134: \n135: ### REQ-007: UpdateSandbox Semantics\n136: \n137: **Requirement:** The system SHALL update only the session JSON value using SET with XX (key must exist). The system SHALL NOT modify expiry or last-activity ZSET entries in this operation.\n138: \n139: #### Scenario: Update existing session\n140: - **GIVEN** session `abc` exists with JSON value V1\n141: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` with updated data succeeds\n142: - **THEN** JSON value is V2; `session:expiry` and `session:last_activity` unchanged\n143: \n144: #### Scenario: Missing key on update\n145: - **GIVEN** session key `session:abc` does not exist\n146: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` runs\n147: - **THEN** Redis: `SETXX` returns false → error; Valkey: response not `\"OK\"` → error\n148: \n149: ---\n150: \n151: ### REQ-008: DeleteSandboxBySessionID Cleanup\n152: \n153: **Requirement:** The system SHALL delete session key and remove session id from both sorted sets in one pipeline/multi.\n154: \n155: #### Scenario: Full removal\n156: - **GIVEN** an existing session in main key + both ZSETs\n157: - **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, id)` succeeds\n158: - **THEN** GET `session:{id}` returns not found AND both ZSETs no longer contain the member\n159: \n160: ---\n161: \n162: ### REQ-009: List Loaders Tolerate Missing Keys\n163: \n164: **Requirement:** When listing by ZSET returns session ids, the system SHALL load JSON per id; SHALL skip entries where the string key is missing without failing the whole batch.\n165: \n166: #### Scenario: Orphan ZSET member skipped\n167: - **GIVEN** a session id in `session:expiry` ZSET without a string value\n168: - **WHEN** `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx, ids)` runs\n169: - **THEN** that id is omitted from the returned slice (no error)\n170: \n171: #### Scenario: Partial MGET success\n172: - **GIVEN** 5 session ids in ZSET; 3 have string values, 2 are orphaned\n173: - **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, 10)` runs\n174: - **THEN** returns slice of 3 sandboxes (orphans skipped silently)\n175: \n176: ---\n177: \n178: ### REQ-010: UpdateSessionLastActivity Preconditions\n179: \n180: **Requirement:** The system SHALL reject empty session id. If `at` is zero time, the system SHALL use `time.Now()`. The system SHALL verify the session key exists before ZADD; if absent, SHALL return `ErrNotFound`.\n181: \n182: #### Scenario: Empty session id rejected\n183: - **GIVEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"\", time.Now())`\n184: - **WHEN** called\n185: - **THEN** error indicates session id is empty\n186: \n187: #### Scenario: Zero time uses Now\n188: - **GIVEN** session `abc` exists; `at = time.Time{}`\n189: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"abc\", time.Time{})` is called\n190: - **THEN** ZADD uses `time.Now().Unix()` as score\n191: \n192: #### Scenario: Activity bump for unknown session\n193: - **GIVEN** no `session:{id}` key\n194: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, id, time.Now())` is called\n195: - **THEN** return `ErrNotFound` (no ZADD performed)\n196: \n197: ---\n198: \n199: ### REQ-011: Provider Selection via STORE_TYPE\n200: \n201: **Requirement:** The system SHALL read `STORE_TYPE` case-insensitively; if unset, SHALL default to `redis`. Supported values SHALL be `redis` and `valkey`; any other value SHALL fail initialization.\n202: \n203: #### Scenario: Default redis\n204: - **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is not set\n205: - **WHEN** `Storage()` first initializes\n206: - **THEN** Redis implementation is constructed\n207: \n208: #### Scenario: Case-insensitive store type\n209: - **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE=REDIS` or `STORE_TYPE=Redis`\n210: - **WHEN** `Storage()` initializes\n211: - **THEN** Redis implementation is constructed\n212: \n213: #### Scenario: Valkey selected\n214: - **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE=valkey`\n215: - **WHEN** `Storage()` initializes\n216: - **THEN** Valkey implementation is constructed\n217: \n218: #### Scenario: Invalid store type fails\n219: - **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE=memcached`\n220: - **WHEN** `Storage()` initializes\n221: - **THEN** initialization fails with error indicating unsupported store type\n222: \n223: ---\n224: \n225: ### REQ-012: Redis Environment and Password Policy\n226: \n227: **Requirement:** The system SHALL require `REDIS_ADDR`. The system SHALL require non-empty `REDIS_PASSWORD` unless `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is set case-insensitively to `false`.\n228: \n229: #### Scenario: Password required by default\n230: - **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` set, `REDIS_PASSWORD` empty, `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` unset\n231: - **WHEN** Redis store initializes\n232: - **THEN** initialization fails with error stating password required\n233: \n234: #### Scenario: Password disabled explicitly\n235: - **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` set, `REDIS_PASSWORD` empty, `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`\n236: - **WHEN** Redis store initializes\n237: - **THEN** connection proceeds with empty password\n238: \n239: #### Scenario: Password provided\n240: - **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` and `REDIS_PASSWORD` both set\n241: - **WHEN** Redis store initializes\n242: - **THEN** connection uses provided password\n243: \n244: ---\n245: \n246: ### REQ-013: Valkey Environment and Options\n247: \n248: **Requirement:** The system SHALL require `VALKEY_ADDR` (comma-separated addresses split for `InitAddress`). The system SHALL require non-empty `VALKEY_PASSWORD` unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`. The system SHALL set `DisableCache` true when `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` parses as true; SHALL set `ForceSingleClient` true when `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` parses as true.\n249: \n250: #### Scenario: Comma-separated addresses\n251: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR=node1:6379,node2:6379,node3:6379`\n252: - **WHEN** Valkey client options are built\n253: - **THEN** `InitAddress` contains three addresses\n254: \n255: #### Scenario: Optional client flags — DisableCache\n256: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true`\n257: - **WHEN** Valkey client options are built\n258: - **THEN** `DisableCache` is true on `ClientOption`\n259: \n260: #### Scenario: Optional client flags — ForceSingle\n261: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=true`\n262: - **WHEN** Valkey client options are built\n263: - **THEN** `ForceSingleClient` is true on `ClientOption`\n264: \n265: #### Scenario: Invalid boolean falls back to false\n266: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=maybe`\n267: - **WHEN** Valkey client options are built\n268: - **THEN** `DisableCache` is false (ParseBool fails)\n269: \n270: ---\n271: \n272: ### REQ-014: Singleton Access\n273: \n274: **Requirement:** The system SHALL expose `func Storage() Store` using `sync.Once`; failed init SHALL log fatal via klog.\n275: \n276: #### Scenario: Single initialization\n277: - **GIVEN** multiple goroutines call `Storage()` concurrently\n278: - **WHEN** they run at the same time\n279: - **THEN** `initStore` executes exactly once\n280: \n281: #### Scenario: Fatal on init failure\n282: - **GIVEN** invalid configuration (e.g., missing `REDIS_ADDR`)\n283: - **WHEN** `Storage()` is called\n284: - **THEN** klog.Fatalf is invoked with error message\n285: \n286: ---\n287: \n288: ## Data Types\n289: \n290: ### SandboxInfo (from `pkg/common/types`)\n291: \n292: ```go\n293: type SandboxInfo struct {\n294:     Kind             string              `json:\"kind\"`\n295:     SandboxID        string              `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n296:     SandboxNamespace string              `json:\"sandboxNamespace\"`\n297:     Name             string              `json:\"name\"`\n298:     EntryPoints      []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n299:     SessionID        string              `json:\"sessionId\"`\n300:     CreatedAt        time.Time           `json:\"createdAt\"`\n301:     ExpiresAt        time.Time           `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n302:     Status           string              `json:\"status\"`\n303: }\n304: \n305: type SandboxEntryPoint struct {\n306:     Path     string `json:\"path\"`\n307:     Protocol string `json:\"protocol\"`\n308:     Endpoint string `json:\"endpoint\"`\n309: }\n310: ```\n311: \n312: ---\n313: \n314: ## Key Patterns\n315: \n316: | Component | Pattern |\n317: |-----------|---------|\n318: | Session document | `session:{sessionID}` |\n319: | Expiry index | `session:expiry` (ZSET: member=sessionID, score=ExpiresAt.Unix()) |\n320: | Last-activity index | `session:last_activity` (ZSET: member=sessionID, score=LastActivity.Unix()) |\n321: \n322: ---\n323: \n324: ## Error Definitions\n325: \n326: ```go\n327: var ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"store: not found\")\n328: ```\n329: \n330: ---\n331: \n332: ## Environment Variables\n333: \n334: | Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n335: |----------|----------|---------|-------|\n336: | `STORE_TYPE` | No | `redis` | Case-insensitive; `redis` or `valkey` |\n337: | `REDIS_ADDR` | Yes (if redis) | — | Redis server address |\n338: | `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Yes unless disabled | — | Empty allowed if `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` |\n339: | `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Case-insensitive; set to `false` to allow empty password |\n340: | `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes (if valkey) | — | Comma-separated addresses |\n341: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Yes unless disabled | — | Empty allowed if `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` |\n342: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Case-insensitive |\n343: | `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | `false` | ParseBool; enables `DisableCache` if true |\n344: | `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | `false` | ParseBool; enables `ForceSingleClient` if true |\n345: \n346: ---\n347: \n348: ## Implementation Notes\n349: \n350: ### Redis Client\n351: - Library: `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9`\n352: - Type: `*redisv9.Client`\n353: - Pipeline: Used for `StoreSandbox`, `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`\n354: \n355: ### Valkey Client\n356: - Library: `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`\n357: - Type: `valkey.Client`\n358: - MGET: Used in `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` (requires same slot deployment consideration)\n359: \n360: ### Zero-Limit Handling\n361: - `ListExpiredSandboxes` / `ListInactiveSandboxes` with `limit <= 0` returns `nil, nil`\n362: \n363: ---\n364: \n365: ## Acceptance Checklist\n366: \n367: - [ ] `pkg/store/store.go` — Store interface with 9 methods + `ErrNotFound`\n368: - [ ] `pkg/store/singleton.go` — `Storage()`, `initStore()`, provider constants\n369: - [ ] `pkg/store/store_redis.go` — Redis implementation with pipeline operations\n370: - [ ] `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` — Valkey implementation with DoMulti operations\n371: - [ ] `pkg/common/types/sandbox.go` — `SandboxInfo`, `SandboxEntryPoint` types\n372: - [ ] Unit tests for all 14 requirements with GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios\n373: - [ ] Integration tests with real Redis and Valkey instances\n\n(End of file - total 373 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification — AR-012: Session Store Interface\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** `pkg/store`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S  \n**Type:** New feature — Session persistence layer for sandbox orchestration\n\n---\n\n## Requirements & Scenarios\n\n### REQ-001: Store Interface Contract\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a `Store` interface implemented by Redis and Valkey providers with methods: `Ping`, `GetSandboxBySessionID`, `StoreSandbox`, `UpdateSandbox`, `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`, `ListExpiredSandboxes`, `ListInactiveSandboxes`, `UpdateSessionLastActivity`, and `Close`.\n\n#### Scenario: Ping verifies connectivity\n- **GIVEN** a healthy Redis/Valkey server\n- **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775853665162,"end":1775853665189}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775853665199,"sessionID":"ses_286dfbbecffeOwTX0YtXPNLrkv","part":{"id":"prt_d792066f4001u4YeeApCDoHCvB","messageID":"msg_d79205c5d001jIsCynWlTG0ZT3","sessionID":"ses_286dfbbecffeOwTX0YtXPNLrkv","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_95b1b7ba60234cbc8a06fae5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-012/README.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-012/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-012 — 会话存储接口定义\n2: \n3: **Module:** pkg/store  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** S\n6: \n7: ## Summary\n8: \n9: Define the session storage interface for the pkg/store module.\n10: \n11: ## Status\n12: \n13: - [ ] Scaffold directory structure\n14: - [ ] Define session storage interface\n15: - [ ] Add unit tests\n16: - [ ] Add integration tests\n17: \n18: ## Notes\n19: \n20: See `notes/` directory for implementation notes and decisions.\n21: \n22: ## Source Files\n23: \n24: See `src/` directory for source code changes.\n\n(End of file - total 24 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-012 — 会话存储接口定义\n\n**Module:** pkg/store  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S\n\n## Summary\n\nDefine the session storage interface for the pkg/store module.\n\n## Status\n\n- [ ] Scaffold directory structure\n- [ ] Define session storage interface\n- [ ] Add unit tests\n- [ ] Add integration tests\n\n## Notes\n\nSee `notes/` directory for implementation notes and decisions.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-012/README.md","time":{"start":1775853665153,"end":1775853665198}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775853665203,"sessionID":"ses_286dfbbecffeOwTX0YtXPNLrkv","part":{"id":"prt_d79206c94001dodZMV2v0uAjv6","messageID":"msg_d79205c5d001jIsCynWlTG0ZT3","sessionID":"ses_286dfbbecffeOwTX0YtXPNLrkv","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_1af0f1ced0474e0c8d9e7290","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-012/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-012/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-012 — Session Storage Interface Definition Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-012 — Session Storage Interface Definition |\n8: | Module | `pkg/store` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | S |\n11: | Design Stage | ST-3 (Completed) |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Atomic Tasks\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: Core Interface Definition\n18: \n19: - [ ] **TASK-001**: Define `Store` interface in `pkg/store/store.go`\n20:   - Method: `Ping(ctx context.Context) error`\n21:   - Method: `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n22:   - Method: `StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error`\n23:   - Method: `UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error`\n24:   - Method: `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error`\n25:   - Method: `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n26:   - Method: `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n27:   - Method: `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error`\n28:   - Method: `Close() error`\n29: \n30: - [ ] **TASK-002**: Define `ErrNotFound` sentinel error in `pkg/store/store.go`\n31:   - Error message: `\"store: not found\"`\n32:   - Used when session key is absent on read\n33:   - Used when last-activity update targets missing session\n34: \n35: - [ ] **TASK-003**: Define key pattern constants in `pkg/store/store.go`\n36:   - `sessionPrefix = \"session:\"`\n37:   - `expiryIndexKey = \"session:expiry\"`\n38:   - `lastActivityIndexKey = \"session:last_activity\"`\n39: \n40: ### Phase 2: Singleton Pattern\n41: \n42: - [ ] **TASK-010**: Create `pkg/store/singleton.go`\n43:   - Define `provider Store` package variable\n44:   - Define `initStoreOnce = &sync.Once{}`\n45: \n46: - [ ] **TASK-011**: Implement `Storage()` function in `pkg/store/singleton.go`\n47:   - Calls `initStoreOnce.Do(initStore)`\n48:   - Returns `provider` instance\n49:   - Thread-safe singleton access\n50: \n51: - [ ] **TASK-012**: Implement `initStore()` function in `pkg/store/singleton.go`\n52:   - Read `STORE_TYPE` environment variable (case-insensitive)\n53:   - Default to `\"redis\"` if unset\n54:   - Validate: only `\"redis\"` or `\"valkey\"` allowed\n55:   - Call `makeRedisOptions()` or `makeValkeyOptions()` based on type\n56:   - Construct Redis or Valkey store instance\n57:   - Log fatal via `klog.Fatalf(\"init store failed: %v\", err)` on error\n58: \n59: - [ ] **TASK-013**: Define provider type constants in `pkg/store/singleton.go`\n60:   - `redisStoreType = \"redis\"`\n61:   - `valkeyStoreType = \"valkey\"`\n62: \n63: ### Phase 3: Redis Implementation\n64: \n65: - [ ] **TASK-020**: Create `pkg/store/store_redis.go`\n66:   - Define `redisStore` struct with fields:\n67:     - `cli *redisv9.Client` (from `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9`)\n68:     - `sessionPrefix string`\n69:     - `expiryIndexKey string`\n70:     - `lastActivityIndexKey string`\n71: \n72: - [ ] **TASK-021**: Implement `makeRedisOptions()` function\n73:   - Read `REDIS_ADDR` environment variable (required)\n74:   - Read `REDIS_PASSWORD` environment variable\n75:   - Read `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` (default `\"true\"`, case-insensitive compare to `\"false\"`)\n76:   - Return `*redisv9.Options` with `Addr` and `Password`\n77:   - Error if `REDIS_ADDR` empty or password required but empty\n78: \n79: - [ ] **TASK-022**: Implement `NewRedisStore()` constructor\n80:   - Takes `*redisv9.Options`\n81:   - Creates Redis client\n82:   - Returns `&redisStore{cli: client, sessionPrefix: \"...\", expiryIndexKey: \"...\", lastActivityIndexKey: \"...\"}`\n83: \n84: - [ ] **TASK-023**: Implement `redisStore.Ping()` method\n85:   - Execute `PING` command\n86:   - Expect string response `\"PONG\"`\n87:   - Return error if not PONG\n88: \n89: - [ ] **TASK-024**: Implement `redisStore.GetSandboxBySessionID()` method\n90:   - Construct key: `sessionPrefix + sessionID`\n91:   - Execute `GET` command\n92:   - If `redis.Nil` → return `ErrNotFound`\n93:   - Unmarshal JSON to `*types.SandboxInfo`\n94:   - Return error on unmarshal failure\n95: \n96: - [ ] **TASK-025**: Implement `redisStore.StoreSandbox()` method\n97:   - Validate: sandbox not nil, `ExpiresAt` not zero\n98:   - Construct session key\n99:   - Marshal sandbox to JSON\n100:   - Use Pipeline for atomic operations:\n101:     - `SETNX` session key with JSON\n102:     - `ZADD expiryIndexKey` with score=`ExpiresAt.Unix()`, member=sessionID\n103:     - `ZADD lastActivityIndexKey` with score=`time.Now().Unix()`, member=sessionID\n104:   - Execute pipeline\n105:   - Return error if any command fails\n106: \n107: - [ ] **TASK-026**: Implement `redisStore.UpdateSandbox()` method\n108:   - Construct session key\n109:   - Marshal sandbox to JSON\n110:   - Execute `SET key value XX` (key must exist)\n111:   - If key not exists → return error\n112:   - Do NOT modify ZSET entries\n113: \n114: - [ ] **TASK-027**: Implement `redisStore.DeleteSandboxBySessionID()` method\n115:   - Construct session key\n116:   - Use Pipeline for atomic operations:\n117:     - `DEL` session key\n118:     - `ZREM expiryIndexKey` member=sessionID\n119:     - `ZREM lastActivityIndexKey` member=sessionID\n120:   - Execute pipeline\n121:   - Return error on failure\n122: \n123: - [ ] **TASK-028**: Implement `redisStore.ListExpiredSandboxes()` method\n124:   - If `limit <= 0` → return `nil, nil`\n125:   - Execute `ZRANGEBYSCORE expiryIndexKey -inf before.Unix() LIMIT 0 limit`\n126:   - Get session IDs from result\n127:   - Pipeline `GET` for each session key\n128:   - Unmarshal JSON, skip missing keys (tolerate orphaned ZSET members)\n129:   - Return `[]*types.SandboxInfo`\n130: \n131: - [ ] **TASK-029**: Implement `redisStore.ListInactiveSandboxes()` method\n132:   - If `limit <= 0` → return `nil, nil`\n133:   - Execute `ZRANGEBYSCORE lastActivityIndexKey -inf before.Unix() LIMIT 0 limit`\n134:   - Get session IDs from result\n135:   - Pipeline `GET` for each session key\n136:   - Unmarshal JSON, skip missing keys\n137:   - Return `[]*types.SandboxInfo`\n138: \n139: - [ ] **TASK-030**: Implement `redisStore.UpdateSessionLastActivity()` method\n140:   - Validate: sessionID non-empty\n141:   - If `at` is zero time → use `time.Now()`\n142:   - Construct session key\n143:   - Execute `GET` to verify key exists\n144:   - If not exists → return `ErrNotFound`\n145:   - Execute `ZADD lastActivityIndexKey` with score=`at.Unix()`, member=sessionID\n146:   - Return error on failure\n147: \n148: - [ ] **TASK-031**: Implement `redisStore.Close()` method\n149:   - Call `cli.Close()`\n150:   - Return error\n151: \n152: ### Phase 4: Valkey Implementation\n153: \n154: - [ ] **TASK-040**: Create `pkg/store/store_valkey.go`\n155:   - Define `valkeyStore` struct with fields:\n156:     - `cli valkey.Client` (from `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`)\n157:     - `sessionPrefix string`\n158:     - `expiryIndexKey string`\n159:     - `lastActivityIndexKey string`\n160: \n161: - [ ] **TASK-041**: Implement `makeValkeyOptions()` function\n162:   - Read `VALKEY_ADDR` environment variable (required, comma-separated)\n163:   - Split by `,` → `InitAddress` slice\n164:   - Read `VALKEY_PASSWORD` environment variable\n165:   - Read `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` (default `\"true\"`)\n166:   - Read `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` (ParseBool, if true → `DisableCache=true`)\n167:   - Read `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` (ParseBool, if true → `ForceSingleClient=true`)\n168:   - Return `*valkey.ClientOption`\n169:   - Error if `VALKEY_ADDR` empty or password required but empty\n170: \n171: - [ ] **TASK-042**: Implement `NewValkeyStore()` constructor\n172:   - Takes `*valkey.ClientOption`\n173:   - Create Valkey client\n174:   - Returns `&valkeyStore{cli: client, ...}`\n175: \n176: - [ ] **TASK-043**: Implement `valkeyStore.Ping()` method\n177:   - Execute `B().Ping()`\n178:   - Expect string response `\"PONG\"`\n179: \n180: - [ ] **TASK-044**: Implement `valkeyStore.GetSandboxBySessionID()` method\n181:   - Construct key: `sessionPrefix + sessionID`\n182:   - Execute `B().Get().Key(key)`\n183:   - If `IsValkeyNil` → return `ErrNotFound`\n184:   - Unmarshal bytes to `*types.SandboxInfo`\n185: \n186: - [ ] **TASK-045**: Implement `valkeyStore.StoreSandbox()` method\n187:   - Validate: sandbox not nil, `ExpiresAt` not zero\n188:   - Construct session key\n189:   - Marshal sandbox to JSON\n190:   - Use `DoMulti` for atomic operations:\n191:     - `SETNX` session key with JSON\n192:     - `ZADD expiryIndexKey` with score, member\n193:     - `ZADD lastActivityIndexKey` with score, member\n194:   - Check all responses for errors\n195: \n196: - [ ] **TASK-046**: Implement `valkeyStore.UpdateSandbox()` method\n197:   - Construct session key\n198:   - Marshal sandbox to JSON\n199:   - Execute `SET key value XX`\n200:   - Success requires response `ToString() == \"OK\"`\n201: \n202: - [ ] **TASK-047**: Implement `valkeyStore.DeleteSandboxBySessionID()` method\n203:   - Construct session key\n204:   - Use `DoMulti`:\n205:     - `DEL` session key\n206:     - `ZREM expiryIndexKey` member\n207:     - `ZREM lastActivityIndexKey` member\n208: \n209: - [ ] **TASK-048**: Implement `valkeyStore.ListExpiredSandboxes()` method\n210:   - If `limit <= 0` → return `nil, nil`\n211:   - Execute `Zrangebyscore` with `Min(\"-inf\")`, `Max(fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix()))`, `Limit(0, limit)`\n212:   - Get session IDs\n213:   - Use `Mget` to load all session keys (comment: keys should be in same slot)\n214:   - Unmarshal JSON, skip empty strings\n215: \n216: - [ ] **TASK-049**: Implement `valkeyStore.ListInactiveSandboxes()` method\n217:   - Same as `ListExpiredSandboxes` but on `lastActivityIndexKey`\n218: \n219: - [ ] **TASK-050**: Implement `valkeyStore.UpdateSessionLastActivity()` method\n220:   - Validate: sessionID non-empty\n221:   - If `at` is zero → use `time.Now()`\n222:   - Execute `Exists` key → must return 1\n223:   - If 0 → return `ErrNotFound`\n224:   - Execute `Zadd` with timestamp\n225: \n226: - [ ] **TASK-051**: Implement `valkeyStore.Close()` method\n227:   - Call `vs.cli.Close()`\n228:   - Return nil\n229: \n230: ### Phase 5: Helper Functions\n231: \n232: - [ ] **TASK-060**: Implement `sessionKey(sessionID string)` helper\n233:   - Returns `sessionPrefix + sessionID`\n234: \n235: - [ ] **TASK-061**: Implement `marshalSandboxInfo(info *types.SandboxInfo)` helper\n236:   - Marshal to JSON string\n237:   - Return error on failure\n238: \n239: - [ ] **TASK-062**: Implement `unmarshalSandboxInfo(data string, info *types.SandboxInfo)` helper\n240:   - Unmarshal from JSON string\n241:   - Return error on failure\n242: \n243: ### Phase 6: Testing (TDD)\n244: \n245: #### Unit Tests - Interface Contract\n246: \n247: - [ ] **TEST-001**: Create `pkg/store/store_test.go`\n248:   - Test `ErrNotFound` error message equals `\"store: not found\"`\n249: \n250: - [ ] **TEST-002**: Test `sessionKey()` function\n251:   - Given: sessionID `\"abc\"`\n252:   - When: `sessionKey(\"abc\")` called\n253:   - Then: returns `\"session:abc\"`\n254: \n255: - [ ] **TEST-003**: Test `marshalSandboxInfo()` with valid sandbox\n256: 