es exactly once, all get same instance\n395: \n396: - [ ] **TEST-052**: Test `initStore()` with `STORE_TYPE` unset\n397:   - Given: `STORE_TYPE` not set\n398:   - When: `initStore()` called\n399:   - Then: creates Redis store\n400: \n401: - [ ] **TEST-053**: Test `initStore()` with `STORE_TYPE=redis` (case-insensitive)\n402:   - Given: `STORE_TYPE=\"REDIS\"`\n403:   - When: `initStore()` called\n404:   - Then: creates Redis store\n405: \n406: - [ ] **TEST-054**: Test `initStore()` with `STORE_TYPE=valkey` (case-insensitive)\n407:   - Given: `STORE_TYPE=\"VALKEY\"`\n408:   - When: `initStore()` called\n409:   - Then: creates Valkey store\n410: \n411: - [ ] **TEST-055**: Test `initStore()` with invalid `STORE_TYPE`\n412:   - Given: `STORE_TYPE=\"invalid\"`\n413:   - When: `initStore()` called\n414:   - Then: logs fatal error\n415: \n416: #### Integration Tests - Redis\n417: \n418: - [ ] **TEST-060**: Create `pkg/store/store_redis_integration_test.go`\n419:   - Requires Docker Redis or testcontainers\n420: \n421: - [ ] **TEST-061**: Integration test `redisStore.Ping()` with real Redis\n422: \n423: - [ ] **TEST-062**: Integration test `redisStore.StoreSandbox()` → `GetSandboxBySessionID()`\n424:   - Store sandbox\n425:   - Retrieve by session ID\n426:   - Verify fields match\n427: \n428: - [ ] **TEST-063**: Integration test `redisStore.UpdateSandbox()` XX semantics\n429:   - Store sandbox\n430:   - Update sandbox\n431:   - Verify updated fields\n432:   - Try update non-existent → expect error\n433: \n434: - [ ] **TEST-064**: Integration test `redisStore.DeleteSandboxBySessionID()` cleanup\n435:   - Store sandbox\n436:   - Delete\n437:   - Verify GET returns `ErrNotFound`\n438:   - Verify ZSETs don't contain session ID\n439: \n440: - [ ] **TEST-065**: Integration test `redisStore.ListExpiredSandboxes()`\n441:   - Store multiple sandboxes with different expiry times\n442:   - Query with `before` time\n443:   - Verify correct sandboxes returned\n444: \n445: - [ ] **TEST-066**: Integration test `redisStore.ListInactiveSandboxes()`\n446:   - Store multiple sandboxes, update some with `UpdateSessionLastActivity`\n447:   - Query with `before` time\n448:   - Verify correct sandboxes returned\n449: \n450: - [ ] **TEST-067**: Integration test ZSET index consistency under concurrent operations\n451:   - Multiple goroutines Store/Delete concurrently\n452:   - Verify ZSET indices remain consistent\n453: \n454: #### Integration Tests - Valkey\n455: \n456: - [ ] **TEST-070**: Create `pkg/store/store_valkey_integration_test.go`\n457:   - Requires Docker Valkey or testcontainers\n458: \n459: - [ ] **TEST-071**: Integration test `valkeyStore.Ping()` with real Valkey\n460: \n461: - [ ] **TEST-072**: Integration test `valkeyStore.StoreSandbox()` → `GetSandboxBySessionID()`\n462: \n463: - [ ] **TEST-073**: Integration test `valkeyStore.DeleteSandboxBySessionID()` cleanup\n464: \n465: - [ ] **TEST-074**: Integration test `valkeyStore.ListExpiredSandboxes()`\n466: \n467: - [ ] **TEST-075**: Integration test `valkeyStore.ListInactiveSandboxes()`\n468: \n469: ### Phase 7: Documentation\n470: \n471: - [ ] **DOC-001**: Add package documentation to `pkg/store/doc.go`\n472:   - Package overview\n473:   - Store interface contract\n474:   - Redis and Valkey backend support\n475:   - Singleton access pattern\n476:   - Configuration via environment variables\n477: \n478: - [ ] **DOC-002**: Add godoc comments to `Store` interface methods\n479:   - Document parameters and return values\n480:   - Document error conditions\n481:   - Include `ErrNotFound` semantics\n482: \n483: - [ ] **DOC-003**: Add godoc comments to `redisStore` methods\n484:   - Document Redis command patterns used\n485:   - Document pipeline atomicity\n486: \n487: - [ ] **DOC-004**: Add godoc comments to `valkeyStore` methods\n488:   - Document Valkey API patterns used\n489:   - Document DoMulti atomicity\n490: \n491: - [ ] **DOC-005**: Document key patterns in code comments\n492:   - `session:{id}` for JSON storage\n493:   - `session:expiry` ZSET for expiry index\n494:   - `session:last_activity` ZSET for activity index\n495: \n496: - [ ] **DOC-006**: Document ZSET score semantics\n497:   - Expiry score = `ExpiresAt.Unix()`\n498:   - Last activity score = `LastActivityAt.Unix()`\n499: \n500: - [ ] **DOC-007**: Document environment variables in `README.md` or code comments\n501:   - All `REDIS_*` variables\n502:   - All `VALKEY_*` variables\n503:   - `STORE_TYPE` selection\n504:   - Default values and required status\n505: \n506: - [ ] **DOC-008**: Add example usage in doc.go or example test\n507:   - Initialize store via `Storage()`\n508:   - Call `Ping()` to verify connectivity\n509:   - Call `StoreSandbox()` to persist sandbox\n510:   - Call `GetSandboxBySessionID()` to retrieve\n511: \n512: ---\n513: \n514: ## Acceptance Criteria\n515: \n516: - [ ] `Store` interface matches exact signatures from design spec\n517: - [ ] `ErrNotFound` error returned consistently for missing sessions\n518: - [ ] Redis implementation uses `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9`\n519: - [ ] Valkey implementation uses `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`\n520: - [ ] `Storage()` singleton initializes exactly once under concurrent access\n521: - [ ] Provider selection respects `STORE_TYPE` case-insensitivity\n522: - [ ] Default provider is `redis` when `STORE_TYPE` unset\n523: - [ ] Password-optional mode works for both backends\n524: - [ ] ZSET indices remain consistent after store/update/delete operations\n525: - [ ] `StoreSandbox()` uses pipeline/DoMulti for atomic index updates\n526: - [ ] `UpdateSandbox()` uses SET XX semantics (key must exist)\n527: - [ ] `DeleteSandboxBySessionID()` removes key and ZSET members atomically\n528: - [ ] `ListExpiredSandboxes()` uses ZRANGEBYSCORE on expiry index\n529: - [ ] `ListInactiveSandboxes()` uses ZRANGEBYSCORE on last_activity index\n530: - [ ] List methods tolerate orphaned ZSET members (skip missing keys)\n531: - [ ] `UpdateSessionLastActivity()` verifies key exists before ZADD\n532: - [ ] All environment variables documented and tested\n533: - [ ] All unit tests pass\n534: - [ ] Integration tests pass with real Redis and Valkey\n535: - [ ] Godoc documentation complete\n536: \n537: ---\n538: \n539: ## Dependencies\n540: \n541: | Dependency | Source | Usage |\n542: |------------|--------|-------|\n543: | `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | External | Redis client library |\n544: | `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | External | Valkey client library |\n545: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | External | Structured logging |\n546: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | Internal | `SandboxInfo` type |\n547: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/types` | Internal | SandboxInfo alias source |\n548: \n549: ---\n550: \n551: ## Implementation Order\n552: \n553: ```\n554: TASK-001 → TASK-002 → TASK-003\n555:               ↓\n556: TASK-010 → TASK-011 → TASK-012 → TASK-013\n557:               ↓\n558: TASK-020 → TASK-021 → TASK-022 → TASK-023 → ... → TASK-031\n559:               ↓\n560: TASK-040 → TASK-041 → TASK-042 → TASK-043 → ... → TASK-051\n561:               ↓\n562: TASK-060 → TASK-061 → TASK-062\n563:               ↓\n564: TEST-001 → ... → TEST-075\n565:               ↓\n566: DOC-001 → ... → DOC-008\n567: ```\n\n(End of file - total 567 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-012 — Session Storage Interface Definition Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-012 — Session Storage Interface Definition |\n| Module | `pkg/store` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | S |\n| Design Stage | ST-3 (Completed) |\n\n---\n\n## Atomic Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Core Interface Definition\n\n- [ ] **TASK-001**: Define `Store` interface in `pkg/store/store.go`\n  - Method: `Ping(ctx context.Context) error`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-012/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775853665159,"end":177